#readme
🔹 1. Problem Statement
People still face issues while planning trips:

Information scattered across platforms
No unified system for booking tours, hotels, and activities
Lack of personalization
Manual processes for tour operators
👉 Problem Statement: Design and develop a Tour Booking System that allows users to search, compare, and book tours seamlessly, while enabling admins/operators to manage listings, bookings, and users efficiently.

🔹 2. Roles Required in Team (4 Members)
You don’t need fancy titles—keep it practical:

👩‍💻 1. Frontend Developer
UI/UX design
Pages: Home, Search, Booking, Dashboard
Tech: React
👨‍💻 2. Backend Developer
APIs (login, booking, payment)
Business logic
Tech: Spring Boot / Node.js
🧠 3. Database & Integration Engineer
Database design (users, bookings, tours)
Payment gateway integration
Tech: MySQL / MongoDB
🧪 4. QA + DevOps + Project Manager
Testing (manual + automation)
Handles Jira, Agile boards
Deployment (AWS / Render)
💡 In small teams → everyone overlaps a bit.

🔹 3. Tech Stack (Recommended)
🌐 Frontend
React.js
Tailwind CSS / Bootstrap
⚙️ Backend
Node.js (Express) OR Spring Boot (since you know Java 👍)
🗄️ Database
MySQL (structured data)
MongoDB (if flexible schema needed)
🔐 Authentication
JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
💳 Payment (optional but strong feature)
Razorpay / Stripe
☁️ Deployment
Frontend: Vercel / Netlify
Backend: Render / AWS
