🔹 5. Work Division (Agile Style)
Sprint-based approach (2–3 weeks)
🟢 Sprint 1: Setup & Basics
Frontend: UI skeleton (Home, Login)
Backend: User authentication
DB: Tables (Users)
QA: Test login flow
🟡 Sprint 2: Core Features
Frontend: Tour listing page
Backend: Tour APIs
DB: Tours table
QA: Test search/filter
🔵 Sprint 3: Booking System
Frontend: Booking UI
Backend: Booking APIs
DB: Booking table
QA: End-to-end testing
🔴 Sprint 4: Advanced Features
Payment integration
Admin dashboard
Deployment
🔹 6. Jira + Agile Usage
In Jira:
Create:

Epics → Big features (Authentication, Booking, Admin)
Stories → “User can login”
Tasks → API creation, UI design
Bugs → Fix errors
Workflow:
To Do → In Progress → Testing → Done
Agile Practices:
Daily standup (5–10 min)
Sprint planning
Sprint review
🔹 7. Database Design (Basic Idea)
Tables:

Users (id, name, email, password)
Tours (id, destination, price, description)
Bookings (id, user_id, tour_id, date, status)
Payments (id, booking_id, amount, status)
🔹 8. What NEW can you add (to stand out 🚀)
Don’t build a basic CRUD project—add something smart:

💡 Innovation Ideas
1. AI Recommendation System
Suggest tours based on:

Past bookings
Budget
Preferences
2. Chatbot Assistant
Helps users choose trips
3. Dynamic Pricing
Prices change based on demand
4. Review Sentiment Analysis
Analyze reviews (NLP – you know this 😉)
5. Travel Planner
Auto itinerary generator
6. Map Integration
Show tour locations using Google Maps
